ICASA announced that it is moving its head office. The authority said it will move its head office from its current premises in Sandton to 350 Witch-Hazel Avenue, Eco Point Office Park, Centurion. ICASA offices in Sandton will officially cease their operations on 26 October at 17:30 to begin the relocation process. The authority’s new Centurion offices will be open from 29 October 2018 at 08:00. “We have been operating from 164 Katherine Street in Sandton for almost two decades. It is time that we move to another location to improve ICASA accessibility to stakeholders,” said ICASA chairperson Rubben Mohlaloga. ICASA noted that the relocation will not affect any services to licensees, stakeholders, or consumers.